# Permission requests

**Scope:** This file applies **only to this repository**. For the same behavior in **all projects**, add the text from `~/.cursor/user-rules/permission-requests.txt` to **Cursor → Settings → Rules** (User rules). If you use User rules globally, you can delete this file to avoid duplicate instructions in this workspace.

---

Before any step that needs **explicit user approval** (destructive operations, git writes, installs, network access, credentials, paid services, device/signing changes, or anything irreversible), do all of the following **in the same message**:

1. **What** — Name the exact action (command, file change, dashboard click, or scope of edits).
2. **Why** — What it unlocks, what fails or is blocked if skipped, and any meaningful risk or tradeoff.
3. **If declined** — One short line on the alternative or fallback, when one exists.

Then **wait for confirmation** before executing that step, unless the user has already given blanket approval for the current task.

**Example**

> **Permission:** Run `brew install xcodegen` on your Mac.  
> **Why:** Generates `TimeTracker.xcodeproj` from `project.yml` per the migration plan; avoids maintaining a hand-written `pbxproj`. Uses Homebrew and network once.  
> **If you decline:** You can install XcodeGen yourself, or create the Xcode project manually and I will only add source files.

Keep this pattern brief; do not skip the why.
